paragraphs.text: once upon a time, i believe it was a tuesday when i caught your eye, we caught onto somethin'. i hold onto the night, you looked me in the eye and told me you loved me. were you just kidding? 'cause it seems to me this thing is breakin' down.
we almost never speak. i don't feel welcome anymore. baby, what happened? please tell me, 'cause one second it was perfect, now you're halfway out the door.

and i stare he still hasn't called and then you feel so low you can't feel nothin' at all. and you flash back to when he said, "forever and always." oh, oh, and it rains in your bedroom, ever 'ry thing is wrong. it rains when you're here and it rains when you're gone.
